        "treat_en": "Full-mouth rehabilitation: facebow transfer + semi-adjustable articulator mounting; diagnostic wax-up; provisional restorations (6–12 months) to verify OVD, aesthetics, and function; definitive restorations (porcelain-fused-to-metal or monolithic zirconia crowns) after provisional approval; multidisciplinary coordination (perio, endo, ortho as required)",
        "treat_cn": "全口修复重建：面弓转移+半可调殆架上殆；诊断蜡型；临时修复体（6–12个月）验证垂直距离、美观和功能；临时修复获批后放置最终修复体（金属烤瓷冠或单块氧化锆冠）；多学科协作（牙周、牙髓、正畸按需）",
        "line": "first_line",
        "note_en": "Full-mouth rehabilitation is one of the most complex restorative procedures. Diagnostic provisionals are non-negotiable — they prove the concept before irreversible tooth preparation for definitive crowns.",
        "note_cn": "全口修复重建是最复杂的修复手术之一。诊断性临时修复体是不可省略的——它在不可逆的最终冠备牙前验证方案的可行性。",
        "icd": "K03.0, K03.2"
