        "rule": "impaction_complication=none AND patient_age=under_25 AND pericoronitis_history=none",
        "treat_en": "Discuss elective removal vs active monitoring with patient: elective removal in young patients (<25) has better healing outcomes and lower surgical risk; if patient declines — active monitoring with periapical or panoramic radiograph every 2 years to detect late complications; document informed consent for monitoring decision",
        "treat_cn": "与患者讨论择期拔除与主动观察的利弊：年轻患者（<25岁）择期拔除愈合更好、手术风险更低；如患者拒绝——每2年拍根尖片或全景片主动监测以发现迟发并发症；记录知情同意（选择观察）",
        "line": "first_line",
        "note_en": "NICE NG235 (2023) recommends against routine prophylactic removal of impacted wisdom teeth that are pathology-free. However, elective removal in patients under 25 has demonstrably better outcomes if removal is indicated.",
        "note_cn": "NICE NG235（2023年）不推荐对无病理的阻生智齿进行常规预防性拔除。但在25岁以下患者中，如有拔除指征，择期拔除的预后明显更好。",
