        "rule": "complication_type=pericoronitis_localized AND systemic_risk=none",
        "treat_en": "Acute phase: irrigation of pericoronal space with chlorhexidine 0.2%; systemic antibiotics only if systemic signs present (fever, lymphadenopathy); analgesics; once acute inflammation resolved — surgical extraction of causative tooth; do NOT extract during acute phase with spreading infection",
        "treat_cn": "急性期：0.2%氯己定冲洗冠周间隙；仅有全身症状时使用系统性抗生素（发热、淋巴结肿大）；镇痛；急性炎症消退后——手术拔除致病牙；蔓延性感染急性期不得拔牙",
        "line": "first_line",
        "note_en": "Extracting a tooth during an acute spreading infection risks bacteraemia and spread of infection. The standard protocol is to control the acute phase first, then extract after inflammation has resolved.",
        "note_cn": "在急性蔓延性感染期间拔牙有菌血症和感染扩散的风险。标准方案是先控制急性期，炎症消退后再拔牙。",
